Senate Resolution 390
By: Senator James of the 28th
A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing and commending Carlos Rico Walker; and for other purposes.
2 WHEREAS, Carlos Rico Walker, better known as Shawty Lo, was a rapper, songwriter, and
3 producer from Atlanta, Georgia’s, Bowen Homes community; and
4 WHEREAS, in 2003, Shawty Lo formed the Hip Hop group D4L, with fellow Atlanta based
5 rappers Fabio, Mook-B and Stoney; and
6 WHEREAS, the group hit national status in January 2006, when their single “Laffy Taffy”
7 topped the Billboard Hot 100 and went on to be certified Platinum twice by the Recording
8 Industry Association of America; and
9 WHEREAS, in 2007, Shawty Lo began pursuing a solo career with his debut album“Units
10 in the City," which reached number 14 on the U.S. Billboard 200 chart and sold over 160,000
11 copies; and
12 WHEREAS, Shawty Lo is known as the KING of Bankhead, he represented the ingenuity
13 of Bankhead and Bowen Homes as well as diligently contributed to numerous causes that
14 supported the community; and
